x4freetext: - detector
chamber description
Super mirror neutron guide tube
facility of the Kyoto University Reactor
Thermal neutron spectrum. The slow neutron flux at the
exit of the guide tube was about 5 x 10**7 (n/cm2/s).
- Target enrichment is 92.0%.
- Physical-form of target is solid.
- Target-thickness is 0.005 mg/cm**2.
2v2E measurement
Detect light fission fragment and heavy fission
fragment in coincidence.
To obtain velocities of two fragments
Two thin film scintillation detectors (TFD) to
obtain start signal of fragments. Typical thickness of
the TFD was 30 mu-g/cm2
silicon surface barrier detector (SSBD). The
SSBDs with sensitive area of 900 mm2 used to determine
the energy of the fragment. The detection efficiency
of this experimental setup was about 1.7 x 10**(-3).
